## Here is the step by step process to install minikube on Ubuntu or CentOS

1. Launch medium tier instance (t3a.medium - 2vCPU/4 Gig memory)

2. Install kubectl
curl -o kubectl https://amazon-eks.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/1.21.2/2021-07-05/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
chmod +x ./kubectl
mkdir -p $HOME/bin && cp ./kubectl $HOME/bin/kubectl && export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/bin
kubectl version --short --client

3. Install docker

apt-get update -y
apt-get install docker.io -y

4. Install minikube

curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

5. minikube start --vm-driver=none

6. apt-get conntrack // for Debian/Ubuntu OS
6. a) yum install conntrack // for CentOS and RHELOS

7. minikube status

8. kubectl get nodes
